The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, April 28, 2004 				 Boycott threat
																								New Delhi, April 27 (PTI): The All India Imam Association today threatened the social boycott of Syed Ahmad Bukhari if he did not apologise to Muslims for urging the community to give the BJP a chance. Shahi Imam (of Delhis Jama Masjid) Syed Ahmad Bukhari has insulted Muslims by appealing for the BJP. He should apologise to Muslims for hurting their feelings and withdraw his appeal or we will call for his social boycott, association president Maulana Mohammad Sajid Rashidi said.
